Rating: 3
Very good, absolutely great the next day. I agree with the 2002 review about the procedure. I heated the garlic in part of the oil until it was golden, then tossed in the peppers. this made the garlic mellow rather than strong. I used all basil and it was fine. As with most recipes, you can fiddle with the seasonings until it's what you want. I added more lemon and salt. The next day I stirred a couple of spoonsful into a green salad and it was great. This is a keeper and a 4 season dish.

