Rating: 3
This is good as is, and also lends itself well to variations. White or kidney beans (or a combination of both) work well. Basil can be substituted for mint, as someone has already mentioned. Slivered olives can be added, or substituted for the capers.

Rating: 3
Right ingredients, wrong technique - Heat the olive oil in a saucepan until hot, add one clove of chopped garlic and cook until just turning color. Then add the pimientos or roast peppers and toss. Let cool and then add chopped basil (instead of mint)and the drained capers. And yes, it can be made ahead if done this way.

